        <skos:prefLabel xml:lang="en">Klepsydra</skos:prefLabel>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">Sprinkler</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">The klepsydra, or water clock, was used to enforce time limits on speeches in Athenian law courts. The pots were filled to a specific level, and as the water drained from a hole near the bottom, marked off the time limit. Approaching the end of the limit, the stream would have diminished perceptibly as the pressure lessened and would have been apparent not only to the orator but to its listeners.</skos:definition>
